    "abstract": "Let $\\mathcal{E}/\\mathbb{F}_q$ be an elliptic curve, and $P$ a point in $\\mathcal{E}(\\mathbb{F}_q)$ of prime order $\\ell$.\nVélu's formulae let us compute a quotient curve $\\mathcal{E}' = \\mathcal{E}/\\langle{P}\\rangle$ and rational maps defining a quotient isogeny $\\phi: \\mathcal{E} \\to \\mathcal{E}'$ in $\\widetilde{O}(\\ell)$ $\\mathbb{F}_q$-operations, where the $\\widetilde{O}$ is uniform in $q$.\nThis article shows how to compute $\\mathcal{E}'$, and $\\phi(Q)$ for $Q$ in $\\mathcal{E}(\\mathbb{F}_q)$, using only $\\widetilde{O}(\\sqrt{\\ell})$ $\\mathbb{F}_q$-operations, where the $\\widetilde{O}$ is again uniform in $q$.\nAs an application, this article speeds up some computations used in the isogeny-based cryptosystems CSIDH and CSURF.",
